    "body": "This PR avoids Py <-> C back and forth conversions:\r\n\r\nIt will convert code from\r\n\r\n```c\r\n__pyx_t_5 = __Pyx_PyLong_As_int(__pyx_t_4); if (unlikely((__pyx_t_5 == (int)-1) && PyErr_Occurred())) __PYX_ERR(0, 49, __pyx_L1_error)\r\n__Pyx_DECREF(__pyx_t_4); __pyx_t_4 = 0;\r\n__pyx_t_4 = __Pyx_PyLong_From_int(__pyx_t_5); if (unlikely(!__pyx_t_4)) __PYX_ERR(0, 49, __pyx_L1_error)\r\n__Pyx_GOTREF(__pyx_t_4);\r\n```\r\n\r\nto\r\n\r\n```c\r\nif (__Pyx_PyInt_FromNumber(&__pyx_t_4, NULL, 1) < (0)) __PYX_ERR(0, 49, __pyx_L1_error)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere are two areas that this optimization is applied:\r\n1. structs - see `tests/run/struct_conversion.pyx` tests\r\n2. subscripted container types - see #7729\r\n\r\n> [!IMPORTANT] \r\n> Current PR has two major flaws:\r\n> 1. running tests  (`struct_conversion` or `pep526_variable_annotations`) containing mention change are yielding a refnanny error: `REFNANNY: Too many decrefs on line 3266, reference acquired on lines`. The error is related to function `__Pyx_PyInt_FromNumber()` but I have no idea why. I checked the function and decrefs should be OK...\r\n> 2. ~~Current PR does not manage NULL values. Original Py -> C -> Py code is raising `TypeError` on `None` value, the optimized code does not.~~",
    "closed_at": null,
